Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri An Aide-de-camp to a former governor of Imo state, Eberendu Chiimechefulem, his legislative aide, Steve Asinuobi and 12 other aides of Rochas Okorocha, were on Monday granted a N5m bond bail on each of the defendants The magistrate, B.U Adikaibe, who ruled on the bail application made for the release of the defendants also insisted that a traditional ruler in the state must stand in as a surety. READ ALSO: Controversy surrounds Niger students, workers’ release, abducted travellers freed They were arraigned on a six-count charge bordering conspiracy, breach of public peace, possession of firearms, unlawful destruction of the official seal of the Imo State Government, a defamatory action on the social media against the governor of the state with the intent to injure the reputation of the state government and the person of the state governor, and disturbance to a lawful order. Some of the defendants are Eberendu Chimechefulem, Ebere Nwoke, Basil MBA, Ebuka Samuel, Darlington Ibekewe, Obasi Goodluck, Nwaiwu Ndubuisi, Ekpendu Peace, Steve Anisnuobi, and Ebere Nwokeobi. READ ALSO: Beware of APC members dancing on Ige’s grave – Aregbesola While Eddy Onyema was the leading counsel for the defendants, E.S Ibechem was the prosecutor. The magistrate had taken a 15-minute break to enable her rule on the bail application after hearing. Drama ensued when one of the defendants, Darlington Ibekwe, slumped while the magistrate was ruling on the bail application. READ ALSO: Banky W, Adesua Etomi welcome baby boy